Sutphin Boulevard, west side, on line of One Hundred Twelfth Ave. when extended. This set of three views shows the N. Williamson house (old No. 703). The owners of this property are N. Williamson, 1860; J. Williamson, 1873; Wm. Selover, 1896-1913; and now by a Jewish organization maintaining an orphanage therein.

1922.
Views 2 & 3: April 1925.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(1) & (2). N. Williamson house.
(3). Van Siclen farmhouse.
